{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QvqfT4iBpNAY5KvqVwF1eM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I know the structure. I need to create a new file `ElmanProofs/Expressivity/E1HTemporalTheorems.lean`.\n\nKey facts to incorporate:\n1. E1H update `h_t = tanh(W_x·x_t + W_h·h_{t-1} + b)` \n2. For 1D head (d=1), this reduces to scalar tanh dynamics studied in TanhSaturation.lean\n3. The four theorems need to reference TanhSaturation.lean and AttentionPersistence.lean\n\nLet me design the file carefully:\n\n\n- For `e1h_has_depth_T`, I'll show that after T steps the state is a T-fold composition by referencing the structural definition from E1HDefinition.lean\n- For `e1h_can_compute_parity`, I'll construct a 1D E1H head with specific weight settings to compute running parity the same way E88 does, using the tanh saturation properties\n- For `e1h_can_threshold`, I'll use weight matrices with amplification factors to achieve state accumulation and latching behavior\n- The independence of E1H heads is already established in the existing proofs\n\n, so I just need to reference that\n\nNow I'm setting up the Lean file structure. I need to construct an explicit E1H head with dimension 1 to demonstrate the parity computation, being careful about how the input and recurrence weight matrices are defined in the type system.\n\nLooking at the E1H update dynamics, with a 1D head the recurrence becomes `tanh(inputProj[0,0] * x[0] + recurrenceWeight[0,0] * h[0] + bias[0])`, which matches the scalar form `tanh(β * x + α * h + b)` that E88 uses. The connection is that E1H's general matrix operations reduce to exactly this structure in the 1D case, and I can leverage the existing `tanhRecurrence` definition by absorbing the input contribution into the bias term.\n\nNow I'm ready to write out the Lean file, keeping the structural proofs explicit where they're straightforward and using `sorry` only for numerical bounds that would require detailed analysis, following the same approach as the E88 definition.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3068,"cache_read_input_tokens":62821,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3068},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a4cab7ff-a8f7-4313-9e26-f408f8d761a1","uuid":"b4a7264a-418d-4325-ad73-0a1641fc791f"}
