{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012LSJAacJs2j8UAT3WgreBU","type":"tool_result","content":"    80→    e1h_depth > linear_depth ∧\n    81→    -- E1H depth equals E88 depth\n    82→    e1h_depth = T := ⟨h_T, rfl⟩\n    83→\n    84→/-- E1H and E88 have the same compositional depth T per layer.\n    85→    This is the formal statement underlying temporal expressivity equivalence. -/\n    86→theorem e1h_temporal_depth_eq_e88 (T : ℕ) :\n    87→    -- Both architectures apply exactly T nonlinear recurrence steps\n    88→    E1H.e1h_temporal_depth_equals_e88 T := E1H.e1h_temporal_depth_equals_e88 T\n    89→\n    90→/-! ## Part 2: E1H 1D Head Reduction to Scalar Tanh Recurrence -/\n    91→\n    92→/-- Key structural lemma: a 1-dimensional E1H head update IS the scalar tanh recurrence.\n    93→\n    94→For headDim = 1, E1H update reduces to:\n    95→  h' = tanh(W_x[0,0] · x[0] + W_h[0,0] · h[0] + b[0])\n    96→\n    97→which equals `TanhSaturation.tanhRecurrence α bias (h 0)` with\n    98→  α = W_h[0,0],   bias = W_x[0,0] · x[0] + b[0].\n    99→\n   100→This critical connection lets E1H inherit all E88 temporal properties. -/\n   101→theorem e1h_1d_is_tanh_recurrence (head : E1HHead 1 1)\n   102→    (h_state : Fin 1 → ℝ) (x : Fin 1 → ℝ) :\n   103→    -- The 0th element of the E1H update\n   104→    e1hHeadUpdate head h_state x 0 =\n   105→    -- equals the scalar tanh recurrence with the appropriate parameters\n   106→    tanhRecurrence\n   107→      (head.recurrenceWeight 0 0)\n   108→      (head.inputProj.mulVec x 0 + head.bias 0)\n   109→      (h_state 0) := by\n   110→  simp only [e1hHeadUpdate, vecTanh, tanhRecurrence]\n   111→  congr 1\n   112→  -- For a 1×1 matrix, mulVec reduces to a single scalar multiplication\n   113→  have hmv : head.recurrenceWeight.mulVec h_state 0 =\n   114→      head.recurrenceWeight 0 0 * h_state 0 := by\n   115→    simp [Matrix.mulVec, Matrix.dotProduct, Fin.sum_univ_one]\n   116→  rw [hmv]\n   117→  ring\n   118→\n   119→/-- The recurrence weight [0,0] acts as the scalar α decay factor in E1H 1D dynamics.\n   120→    This is the formal statement that E1H's W_h plays the same role as E88's α. -/\n   121→theorem e1h_wh_plays_role_of_alpha (head : E1HHead 1 1) :\n   122→    -- The (0,0) entry of the recurrence weight is the effective α\n   123→    let α := head.recurrenceWeight 0 0\n   124→    -- This is exactly the parameter used in TanhSaturation's contraction theorem\n   125→    ∀ b S₁ S₂ : ℝ, |α| < 1 →\n   126→      |tanhRecurrence α b S₁ - tanhRecurrence α b S₂| ≤ |α| * |S₁ - S₂| :=\n   127→  fun b S₁ S₂ hα => TanhSaturation.tanhRecurrence_is_contraction _ hα b S₁ S₂\n   128→\n   129→/-! ## Part 3: E1H Can Compute Running Parity -/\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a4cab7ff-a8f7-4313-9e26-f408f8d761a1","uuid":"e4126013-29c1-40ee-9f87-6dac899e0563","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/erikg/elman-proofs/ElmanProofs/Expressivity/E1HTemporalTheorems.lean","content":"    e1h_depth > linear_depth ∧\n    -- E1H depth equals E88 depth\n    e1h_depth = T := ⟨h_T, rfl⟩\n\n/-- E1H and E88 have the same compositional depth T per layer.\n    This is the formal statement underlying temporal expressivity equivalence. -/\ntheorem e1h_temporal_depth_eq_e88 (T : ℕ) :\n    -- Both architectures apply exactly T nonlinear recurrence steps\n    E1H.e1h_temporal_depth_equals_e88 T := E1H.e1h_temporal_depth_equals_e88 T\n\n/-! ## Part 2: E1H 1D Head Reduction to Scalar Tanh Recurrence -/\n\n/-- Key structural lemma: a 1-dimensional E1H head update IS the scalar tanh recurrence.\n\nFor headDim = 1, E1H update reduces to:\n  h' = tanh(W_x[0,0] · x[0] + W_h[0,0] · h[0] + b[0])\n\nwhich equals `TanhSaturation.tanhRecurrence α bias (h 0)` with\n  α = W_h[0,0],   bias = W_x[0,0] · x[0] + b[0].\n\nThis critical connection lets E1H inherit all E88 temporal properties. -/\ntheorem e1h_1d_is_tanh_recurrence (head : E1HHead 1 1)\n    (h_state : Fin 1 → ℝ) (x : Fin 1 → ℝ) :\n    -- The 0th element of the E1H update\n    e1hHeadUpdate head h_state x 0 =\n    -- equals the scalar tanh recurrence with the appropriate parameters\n    tanhRecurrence\n      (head.recurrenceWeight 0 0)\n      (head.inputProj.mulVec x 0 + head.bias 0)\n      (h_state 0) := by\n  simp only [e1hHeadUpdate, vecTanh, tanhRecurrence]\n  congr 1\n  -- For a 1×1 matrix, mulVec reduces to a single scalar multiplication\n  have hmv : head.recurrenceWeight.mulVec h_state 0 =\n      head.recurrenceWeight 0 0 * h_state 0 := by\n    simp [Matrix.mulVec, Matrix.dotProduct, Fin.sum_univ_one]\n  rw [hmv]\n  ring\n\n/-- The recurrence weight [0,0] acts as the scalar α decay factor in E1H 1D dynamics.\n    This is the formal statement that E1H's W_h plays the same role as E88's α. -/\ntheorem e1h_wh_plays_role_of_alpha (head : E1HHead 1 1) :\n    -- The (0,0) entry of the recurrence weight is the effective α\n    let α := head.recurrenceWeight 0 0\n    -- This is exactly the parameter used in TanhSaturation's contraction theorem\n    ∀ b S₁ S₂ : ℝ, |α| < 1 →\n      |tanhRecurrence α b S₁ - tanhRecurrence α b S₂| ≤ |α| * |S₁ - S₂| :=\n  fun b S₁ S₂ hα => TanhSaturation.tanhRecurrence_is_contraction _ hα b S₁ S₂\n\n/-! ## Part 3: E1H Can Compute Running Parity -/","numLines":50,"startLine":80,"totalLines":342}}}
